benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/admin/invoices - Trigger an invoice generation for all parked accounts

covered: Valid Payload: The tests include valid inputs (default call TC01) and auditing header scenarios (TC03).
Duplicate Submission: Concurrency test TC18 shows idempotent invoicing (one invoice per parked account).
Large Payloads: Tests with limit 1000 (TC10) and limit 10000 (TC12) cover large data volumes.
Validation: Tests cover missing required header (TC05), invalid offset/limit values (TC06, TC07), extra parameters (TC11), and parameter/header validation (TC14).
Server Error Handling: Service downtime (TC09) and authorization errors (TC08).
Backward Compatibility and Regression: Tests for header parsing (TC16) and older clients (TC17).
gaps: Invalid Payload: No tests validate malformed or missing body fields in the POST payload.
Rate Limiting: No tests for rate limiting/throttling (e.g., 429 responses).
Caching Behavior: No tests around caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control) for POST.
Explicit idempotency test: While TC18 covers duplicates, a dedicated test ensuring idempotent behavior for repeated identical requests could be added.
recommendations: Add tests for invalid payload body content (malformed JSON, missing or invalid body fields).
Add rate-limiting tests (429) under high load scenarios.
Add caching-related tests (ETag and Cache-Control) where applicable.
Add explicit idempotency tests to verify duplicates are not created across repeated identical requests.
Add a test simulating 500 Internal Server Error to complement 503 when server or dependencies fail.
Test with very long header values to ensure header parsing and storage does not fail (Reason/Comment).
